    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PUCCH list size calculation in set_sched_pucch_list\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_sched_pucch_list` function in `gNB_scheduler_primitives.c` was using an incorrect bit shift operation to calculate the PUCCH list size, which caused issues when `max_fb_time` was smaller than `nr_slots_period`. This resulted in insufficient memory allocation for PUCCH scheduling structures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Replaced bit shift calculation with proper ceiling division to determine the number of periods needed to cover `max_fb_time` slots.\n\n### Reproduction\nIn TDD configurations with short periods or when `max_fb_time` is small (e.g., 1-2 slots), the original bit shift calculation would result in:\n1. Insufficient PUCCH list size allocation\n2. Potential buffer overruns when accessing `sched_pucch[pucch_index]` \n3. Incorrect PUCCH scheduling decisions\n\nThe issue manifests as scheduling failures or crashes during UCI reporting, particularly in scenarios with low latency requirements where `max_fb_time` is small.\n"
}